## Fetch Category Detail by Slug

Used on the category listings page (`/lc/[slug]`) to get category name, description, image, and hierarchy.

```tsx
import { useGetCategoryBySlugQuery } from '@/state/categories/api'

const slug = router.query.slug as string

const { data, isLoading, isError } = useGetCategoryBySlugQuery(slug, {
  skip: !slug,
})

const category = data?.category

// If isError after loading — slug is invalid, redirect to /not-found
if (!isLoading && isError) {
  router.replace('/not-found')
}

// Category detail fields
category?.name                    // page title
category?.description             // page description
category?.image                   // hero image / banner
category?.hierarchy               // CategoryHierarchy[] — ancestors for breadcrumb
category?.sub_category            // Category[] — child categories (show as filter chips)
```

**Slug → ID fallback is automatic** inside `state/categories/api.ts`:
1. Tries `getSingleCategoryBySlug`
2. If that fails, extracts the leading number from the slug (`"123-electronics"` → `"123"`) and tries `getSingleCategoryByID`
3. If both fail, returns an error — component handles redirect

